title: Google\Cloud\Dataproc\V1\NodeInitializationAction
name: NodeInitializationAction
description:
Specifies an executable to run on a fully configured node and a timeout period for executable completion.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dataproc.v1.NodeInitializationAction

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.executable_file
params.description: Required. Cloud Storage URI of executable file.

params.name: data.execution_timeout
params.description: Optional. Amount of time executable has to complete. Default is 10 minutes (see JSON representation of Duration). Cluster creation fails with an explanatory error message (the name of the executable that caused the error and the exceeded timeout period) if the executable is not completed at end of the timeout period.
